вНЩ_RвЖРвНЩ_PATH APL2TXT вНЩ_RA;вНЩ_CC;вНЩ_DATA;вНЩ_E;вНЩ_EXT;вНЩ_FILE;вНЩ_L;вНЩ_NAME;вНЩ_NC;вНЩ_OBJ;вНЩ_OW;вНЩ_T;вНЩ_TIE;вНЩ_TIME;вНЩ_TXT;вНЩ_U;вНЩ_V;вОХIO
вНЭ Create a unicode txt file in the supplied directory (вНЩ_PATH) showing the
вНЭ contents of the given function or variable (where 1вКГвНЩ_RA=вНЩ_OBJ) is a cvec
вНЭ name of an object in the current workspace) in a unicode based text file
вНЭ that any text editor can understand without APL+Win.

вНЭ If вНЩ_PATH is '', the file is created in the same path as the current ws.

вНЭ вНЩ_OW (2вКГвНЩ_RA) is a bit indicating behavior if the destination text
вНЭ file exists already (1=overwrite).

вНЭ вНЩ_CC (3вКГвНЩ_RA) is a bit indicating whether or not the resulting file
вНЭ should be case coded or not.  Case codes work like this (from Dyalog's
вНЭ ]LINK.CaseCode documentation):
вНЭ
вНЭ   HelloWorld    - has the uppercase indication
вНЭ   1000010000    - which when reversed is
вНЭ   0000100001    - which is binary for
вНЭ   33 Base 10    - which in octal is
вНЭ   41 Base 8     - so the full name including case code is:
вНЭ   HelloWorld-41

вНЭ   No case code (default): <HelloWorld> -> HelloWorld.txt

вНЭ   With case code: <HelloWorld> -> HelloWorld-41.txt

вНЭ The result is a character vector message indicating success or failure.

вНЭ                вЖУвНЩ_PATH            вЖУвНЩ_OBJ   вЖУвНЩ_OW вЖУвНЩ_CC
вНЭ Used like: MSGвЖР'C:\temp\' APL2TXT 'CMIOTA' 0     0

